deconstructed from her ongoing Moving Off the Land performance, provides a "Gesamtkunstwerk" which transports the viewer into an alternate liquid world inhabited by the "other." This essay reveals how the artist accomplishes the daunting task of making us care deeply about the fragility, feelings, necessity, dependencies, and potential extinction of sea life. It also confirms the emotional affect of the work by publishing selected viewer comments from the Ocean Space guestbook.	\N	1	0	0	\N	\N	EN	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Courtesy of Cynthia Haveson Veloric	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N
