oncessione di Christian Fennesz e Touch Music.</p><p>//</p><p>ENG. 'Narrating Venice with Tiziano Scarpa' is the first podcast from the series 'Nowtilus: Stories from a 21st Century Urban Lagoon' produced by Ocean Space in Venice for TBA21–Academy Radio:</p><p>How do Venetians narrate their city? How do foreign writers describe Venice? The writer Tiziano Scarpa answers these questions through anecdotes and stories related to the city's complex and multifaceted charm.</p><p>'Nowtilus: Stories from an urban lagoon in the 21st century' is a programme of research and investigation into voices revealing a Venice that is, first and foremost, a lagoon in relation to the existence of its inhabitants. 'TBA21–Academy Radio' is a broadcast channel diving into conversations about art, culture, imagination and community, as well as music curated around the oceanic stories of human and non-human collaborations. Created by TBA21–Academy, a cultural organisation investigating environmental injustice through the lens of art, and its initiative Ocean Space, an embassy for the Oceans situated in the Church of San Lorenzo, Venice.</p><p>Music: Christian Fennesz. Songs: Chateau Rouge, Laguna, Rivers of Sand. Album: Venice (2004). Provided by Christian Fennesz and Touch Music.</p>	\N	1	0	0	\N	\N	IT	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Nowtilus: Storie da una laguna urbana del 21esimo secolo	Narrare Venezia con Tiziano Scarpa	1	\N	{"Enrico Bettinello","Tiziano Scarpa"}	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Courtesy of TBA21–Academy	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	https://ocean-archive.org/collection/39	\N	01070000A0E61000000200000001010000800000000000B023406BB933130CCF28400000000000000000010100008047C66AF3FFEA24C0E33785950ABA21400000000000000000	t	\N
