ity. \n\nWe are a part of the whole, connected to the complex breathing apparatus of the planet Earth, and we have to make every possible effort to keep it functioning. Nature, and its survival force, is there to bring us back together, and we shouldn’t forget to listen to it and to the ecosystems around. \n\nIt's through the mutual promise of care we can find solidarity and encouragement. 	\N	1	1	1	\N	\N	EN	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	9:16 digital video	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Courtesy of Aennor	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N
