 Marah Hardt capturing the intimate connections found in and around the ocean. This talk explores some of the ocean's most intimate acts and the impact on these strategies for sex and survival. It highlights the profound ways in which human behaviour disrupts the most vital and ancient acts of sea life, and pauses to consider the consequences as a reminder that hope is not lost.	\N	1	1	1	\N	\N	EN	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	Courtesy of the participant(s) and TBA21–Academy	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	The Waves of the Oh!s and the Ah!s	\N	\N	\N	Ocean Space, Church of San Lorenzo, Venice, Italy	{"Markus Reymann","Francesca Thyssen-Bornemisza","Chus Martínez","Marah Hardt"}	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	https://ocean-archive.org/collection/2	\N	\N	t	\N
