tion 'Spheric Ocean: To Find the Vegan Lion.'\n\nThe expedition took place in March 2018 on board the M/Y Dardanella as part of TBA21–Academy's 'The Current II' fellowship programme. The journey set the space to feel and think differently about the oceans, springing from the urge to reunite thinkers and artists to start a new school of sensing intelligence while exploring the questions: Is the Ocean an art space? Or a future space within the arts? How many waves are in the Ocean? What can we ask the ocean?	\N	1	0	0	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	digital photograph	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	Courtesy of Claudia Comte and TBA21–Academy	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	{3024,4032}	https://ocean-archive.org/collection/5	\N	01070000A0E610000001000000010100008016D6A04288D96540D2B7413C742242C020CCCB79D8B1873F	t	\N
