561	private/eu-central-1:12102e0b-bb96-42f0-9d3c-1df78ee120b2/418b7876-0b02-4d53-b0c4-38683f95c14b/3e39ce10-387b-11ea-a123-5136323128cb-WE_ARE_OCEAN_OMEU.mp4	2972a49554eeae3b4fa9152d7953bfd2cdf38daf154d1040ea51128afb231505163c2896401e97432cbfba3b3fd204ef76a819297e2636e66ae07b7dc9c32dec	\N	\N	73f495bf29be33ed18975b0317228776	\N	2020-01-17 03:27:41.796037+11	2020-04-10 21:54:00.694+10	\N	t	{1,12,32}	{1068,1069,1070,1071,1072,1073,1074,1075,1076,1077}	\N	{DE}	Video	Art	{"ARTPORT_making waves","Lisa Rave"}	418b7876-0b02-4d53-b0c4-38683f95c14b	{"Lisa Rave"}	\N	\N	\N	{TBA21–Academy,"Institute for Advanced Sustainability Studies Potsdam","Stiftung Berliner Sparkasse","Fonds Soziokultur","Marine Regions Forum","The Intergovernmental Oceanographic Commission of UNESCO","The Ocean Decade",Alfred-Wegener-Institut,"Barbara-Zürner-Oberschule Velten","Schule am Berlinickeplatz","Andreas Bolm"}	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	2019	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	CC BY-NC	WE ARE OCEAN - A film made in collaboration with secondary school students in Berlin and in Brandenburg.	\N	\N	This film was made by German artist Lisa Rave in close collaboration with two school classes in Berlin and Brandenburg, Germany (Barbara-Zürner-Oberschule in Velten, Brandenburg  and Schule am Berlinickeplatz in Berlin). During a three-day workshop on the interdependency with the ocean, the students asked questions expressing their doubts, fears, impressions and knowledge. The workshops led to on-camera discussions taking place over two morning sessions between August and September 2019.\n\nARTPORT_making waves commissioned the film as part of the interdisciplinary art project 'WE ARE OCEAN' as a contribution to the 'UN Decade of Ocean Science for Sustainable Development' (2021-2030) and the 'Ocean Literacy Program of IOC-UNESCO' (www.oceandecade.org). These voices are carried around the world with interdisciplinary art components including science and education in Berlin, Brandenburg, Venice, Lisbon, Marseille, Vancouver, Mumbai and Glasgow from 2019-2021. In Berlin and Brandenburg, ARTPORT_making waves commissioned artist Lisa Rave to organize targeted workshops at selected schools for students aged 13 to 17. The results of the workshops and dialogical exchange were discussed with prominent thinkers such as Prof. Dr. Antje Boetius (Alfred-Wegener-Institute), Dr. Thierry Pérez (Institut Pythéas Marseille), Markus Reymann (TBA21–Academy) and artists Michelle-Marie Letelier and Lisa Rave at the 'Marine Regions Forum 2019.' The project was later presented to a broader audience at the 'FUTURIUM Berlin' with interactive interventions of the students, film screenings and a fishbowl panel discussion with Markus Reymann, Prof. Dr. Antje Boetius, Sebastian Unger (Institute for Advanced Sustainability Studies Potsdam) and Dr. Lukas Köhler (Member of the German Parliament). Furthermore, there were similar events organized at CLB Berlin and STATE Studio Berlin with interactive and participatory elements involving young people and the audience.\n\n'WE ARE OCEAN' brings together younger generations with politicians, academics and other decision-makers to think about feasible solutions. The project continues to promote the regular implementation of external scholarly-artistic workshops into the curriculum of schools to provide first-hand knowledge in creative ways and involve the youth in international processes, giving them an active voice.	\N	1	1	0	\N	\N	DE	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Courtesy of Lisa Rave	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N
