ustry media, legal definitions and dictionary entries. The episode hopes to reveal something about how deep sea mining is a contested, polyphonic site, with the future of the seabed and its ecologies up for grabs.\n\n'What is Deep Sea Mining?' is a TBA21–Academy commission developed by Inhabitants (Mariana Silva and Pedro Neves Marques), an online channel for exploratory video and documentary reporting, in collaboration with Margarida Mendes, curator and activist from Lisbon, Portugal, and founding member of Oceano Livre environmental movement against deep sea mining.	\N	1	0	1	\N	\N	EN	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	Courtesy of Inhabitants and TBA21–Academy	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	https://ocean-archive.org/collection/19	\N	\N	t	\N
