iving Marine Resources Belong to Society as a Whole’ (2017), an anthology of works helping us to understand, express and manage environmental issues in new and better ways.	\N	1	0	0	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Courtesy of ­­­­­­­Munan Øvrelid / The Wild Living Marine Resources Belong to Society as a Whole	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	https://ocean-archive.org/collection/18	\N	\N	t	\N
