ea mining on local ecosystems and on the archipelago’s economical reality.\n\n'What is Deep Sea Mining?' is a TBA21–Academy commission developed by Inhabitants (Mariana Silva and Pedro Neves Marques), an online channel for exploratory video and documentary reporting, in collaboration with Margarida Mendes, curator and activist from Lisbon, Portugal, and founding member of Oceano Livre environmental movement against deep sea mining.	\N	1	0	1	\N	\N	PT	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	Courtesy of Inhabitants and TBA21–Academy	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	https://ocean-archive.org/collection/19	\N	\N	t	\N
